The location was perfect. Just a few blocks from downtown. If it wasn’t freezing out (we’re Floridians) we could have totally made the walk to local restaurants and shops. It is also a very nice, quiet neighborhood.
Her home supplied us with everything we could have possibility thought of. Fresh sheets, towels, full dish & silverware sets, crib for our baby, etc. It was all remarkably clean - the whole house!
Check-in process was easy and there were zero communication issues with Kelly or other hosts. She always quickly responded!
We would stay here a million times over! Can’t wait to return❤️

review_text: 615 at Kelley’s was an amazing quite restful stay with a great location downtown and a fitness center a block away. Neighborhood was quite and very family friendly. Kelly’s home very beautiful and nicely decorated. Kitchen was well organized and stocked with everything you need to cook a great home cooked meal with your own groceries of course. Upstairs attic is very spacious and comfortable aswell as private, if you have kids a great playroom with toys and a beautiful doll house. Bathroom in attic has a big tub to bath. Patio was beautifully light up and a great escape from the mesquites while still enjoying the cool night breeze. Highly recommend if hotels make you uncomfortable. Kelly was very responsive and able to be flexible on arrival and staying an extra night. Much appreciated. Truly worth every penny. Will definitely be returning. Kelly’s place is just amazing! You won’t be disappointed.

Stayed with kids
review_text:
This home is beautiful! It is bright, well decorated, and incredibly spacious. The front porch is the perfect place to relax and step into the quiet. The hosts are so quick to respond and incredibly accommodating, they worked with us to get in prior to check in time so we could attend a big family function. The location is awesome.
However, she does note this is her primary residence, what isn't noted is that the fridge is so full of her stuff that you can't put anything in it and the house is full of personal things (including closets and dressers). There isn't anywhere to put your own things, as all surfaces are decorated or covered. There was even a loofah in the shower. It was very awkward and I truly felt like I was staying in someone's home, so we were never able to feel fully comfortable while we were there, because we didn't know what we could touch and use and what we couldn't.
Again, amazing host and home!
